    Bug fix in the CuTe interface MoE GEMM example (#648)
    
    ## Description of bug fix
    
    @mayuyuace discovered that `assert` in the CuTe interface MoE GEMM
    example surprisingly does not work, and hides accuracy failures:
    
    
    https://github.com/intel/sycl-tla/blob/466f5cb0f5a096b6e0abbab55fc121a8f32714aa/examples/12_bmg_moe_gemm_cute_interface/12_bmg_moe_gemm_cute_interface.cpp#L293
    
    I investigated & the accuracy bug was related to sycl kernel launch.
    However, I don't know why assert didn't work, while the following did:
    
     ```c++
     if (helper.verify(activations, weights, outputs) == false) {
        std::cout << "\n\nFailed accuracy verification\n\n";
      }
    ```
    
    ## Additional change for ease-of-use:
    
    This PR also enables support for passing `void` template parameter for copy atoms. In that case, they will be chosen automatically. e.g.
    
    ```c++
            // will automatically choose copy atoms
            MoE::MoEGEMM<void, void, void,
    'R', 'R', 'R'>(activations, weights, scales, outputs, mma,
    num_rows_per_expert_device, num_experts,
                                        gemm_n, gemm_k, scheduler_params);
    
            // manually specified copy atoms
            MoE::MoEGEMM<XE_LOAD_2D<16, 32, 32, 16>,
    XE_LOAD_2D_VNNI<16, 32, 16, 16>, XE_STORE_2D<16, 8, 32>,
    'R', 'R', 'R'>(activations, weights, scales, outputs, mma,
    num_rows_per_expert_device, num_experts,
                                        gemm_n, gemm_k, scheduler_params);
    ```
    
    This was already supported in the example for copy atoms to load canonical `A`, `B` tiles.

