    Fixing trD compute type in the Xe Epilogue (#580)
    
    This PR is to fix the _trD_compute_frag_ type in Xe Epilogue based on
    the type configured in _cst_callbacks_.
    
    ElementOutput in the LinearCombination and ElementOutput in the
    CollectiveEpilogue are two different things.
    ElementOutput in CollectiveEpilogue is always same as ElementD, but the
    ElementOutput in LinearCombination need not to be same as ElementD.
    
    ElementOutput in the LinearCombination represent the output of the
    LinearCombination operation (alpha*AB, beta*C).
    At the same time, ElementOutput/ElementD in the CollectiveEpilogue
    represented the actual output which must be stored back.

