    Refactor CausalMask logic in Flash Attention kernel for better code reuse and potential compiler optimization (#507)
    
    1. Unified Loop Condition: Changed the loop from for (int nblock = 0;
    nblock < nblock_limit - CausalMask; nblock++) to for (int nblock = 0;
    nblock < nblock_limit - 1; nblock++). This standardizes the iteration
    for most blocks, treating the last block more consistently without
    relying on the CausalMask template parameter directly in the main loop
    bound. This could enhance performance in scenarios with large
    nblock_limit, as compilers are more aggressive with optimizations on
    consistent loop bodies.
    2. Shared Logic On The Last Block: Reuse the mmaQK, softmax, and mmaPV
    operations across both the CausalMask and None CausalMask. This
    eliminates code duplication, improves maintainability.
    
