    Avoid warnings about Int (alias template) (#365)
    
    This PR gets rid of these warnings about alias templates:
    ```
    /home/joe/sources/cutlass/include/cute/atom/copy_traits_xe.hpp:413:7: warning: class template argument deduction for alias templates is a C++20 extension [-Wc++20-extensions]
      413 |   Int mma_atom_size_N =
          |       ^
    ```
    
    Basically `Int` is an alias template:
    ```cpp
    template <int v>
    using Int = C<v>;
    ```
    and although the compiler is perfectly capable of determining the
    integer template argument to `Int` from e.g.:
    ```cpp
      Int mma_atom_size_N =
          Int<!TiledCopy::is_convention_MN ? size<1>(mma_atom_shape_2d) : size<0>(mma_atom_shape_2d)>{};
    ```
    it's not permitted under c++17. I chose to solve this by changing to
    `auto`. It would be equally valid to change them to `C`:
    ```cpp
      C mma_atom_size_N = ...
    ```
    or to refactor it like:
    ```cpp
      Int<!TiledCopy::is_convention_MN ? size<1>(mma_atom_shape_2d) : size<0>(mma_atom_shape_2d)> mma_atom_size_N{};
    ```
    but this felt the most readable.
    
    ---------
    
