    Linear layer benchmarks (#307)
    
    This PR defines benchmarks for a linear layer (**RowMajor A, ColumnMajor
    B, per column bias epilogue**) and makes some changes to both the
    benchmarks and the equivalent example
    (`05_pvc_gemm_with_per_col_bias.cpp`) which enable us to execute a batch
    of GEMMs which reuse the same B matrix.
    
    In CuTe terms, re-using a single B matrix for every GEMM in a batch is
    defined by:
    ```cpp
      using StrideB = cute::Stride<int64_t, _1, _0>; // Stride for batch is _0 (re-use the same B matrix)
    ```
    However, our existing examples & benchmarking infrastructure still uses
    CUTLASS 2.x Layout Tags, which make it impossible to define this case.
    As such, this PR introduces quite a few changes where either:
     - a 2.x layout tag is used
     - the assumption of a dense packed matrix breaks this case
    
    For example, the assumption that the 'physical' size of matrix B is `N *
    K * L` is baked in in a few places. These have been generalized by
    redefining them according to the cosize of the layout. Equivalent
    generalizations are made to define the stride between batches.
    
    This PR also introduces the ability to specify an epilogue operation for
    a benchmark GEMM configuration.
    
