    Dequantization Support in Mixed Precision (#279)
    
    This PR adds support for dequantization in mixed precision GEMM.
    Dequantization involves multiplying the narrower matrix type by a scale
    value, and the addition of an optional zero/offset/bias term. Values are
    quantized/dequantized in blocks (e.g. 128 values along the K dimension
    may share a single pair of scale/zero values). This allows efficient
    (lossy) compression of data from a wider type (e.g. `bfloat16`) to a
    narrower type (`int8` in this case).
    
    The implementation in this PR supports either A or B being the narrower
    type, and defines 3 mixed precision modes:
    - `ConvertOnly`: no scale or zero value, simply convert narrower to
    wider type
    - `ConvertAndScale`: convert narrow to wider type, then multiply by
    scale
    - `ConvertAndScaleWithZero`: convert narrow to wider type, then multiply
    by scale and add zero value
    
    The implementation requires that:
    - the scales are stored in MN major format
    - the 'group size' (i.e. size of the block of values which share a
    scale/zero value) is a multiple of the WorkgroupTile K size.
    
    This PR provides a functionally complete implementation, but performance
    improvements are needed. I am raising this PR now to avoid more painful
    merge conflicts down the line.
    
