    Generalising dual gemm (#288)
    
    Dual GEMM operation can be used in several AI models. Some of them are
    list as follow
    
    **Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP) blocks in Transformers**
    
    - For Transformer-based models like GPT, BERT, T5, LLaMA, etce in the
    form of
    
    ```
    H0= Activation(XW0)
    H1=XW1
    Y=H0.H1
    ```
    
     **Gated Activation Units (GLU, SwiGLU, GEGLU) :**
    
    - SwiGLU (used in PaLM, GPT-4, Gemma, etc.)
    - GEGLU (used in T5, BERT, etc.)
    e.g.
    ```
    G= XW0
    V=XW1
    Y=SWISH(G0).V
    ```
    
    **Vision Transformers (ViTs) and Efficient CNNs**
    
    
    ```
    H0= GELU(XW0)
    H1=XW1
    Y=H0.H1
    ```
    This PR allows to generelize dual gemm to capture several Activation and
    elementwise operations on the outputs
    
